  "title": "IT officer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ol><li>Maintain daily IT infrastructure for the company and building;</li><li>Manage and maintain low-voltage systems, including network\n     cabling, CCTV, and access control;</li><li>Perform basic configuration and maintenance of servers and\n     network equipment (routers, switches);</li><li>Install, configure, and troubleshoot computers, printers, and\n     office equipment;</li><li>Assist in IT system optimization, network planning, and\n     upgrades;</li><li>Coordinate with external IT vendors when necessary.</li></ol><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ol><li>Diploma or above in Computer Science, IT, or related fields;</li><li>Familiar with low-voltage systems, network architecture, and\n     basic server management;</li><li>Prior experience in corporate IT support or facility IT\n     operations is an advantage;</li><li>Strong problem-solving and analytical skills;</li><li>Proactive, responsible, and good communication skills.</li></ol>",
